        "content": "<p>I have the goal of proving <code>↑p / ↑q = b</code> and I have the hypothesis h₃ that states that <code>↑p &lt; ↑q * b</code>. I feel like I should be able to use the statement <code>exact div_lt_iff_lt_mul'.2 h₃,</code> but when I do I get this weird error.<br>\n<a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/3KXlUCH1Z-KFMNlT3XIpwTo9/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/3KXlUCH1Z-KFMNlT3XIpwTo9/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/3121/3KXlUCH1Z-KFMNlT3XIpwTo9/image.png\"></a></div><p>Surely these are the same type though?</p>",
        "id": 377102955,
        "sender_full_name": "shortc1rcuit",
        "timestamp": 1689884316
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>That sounds like you're using the wrong lemma. What are <code>p</code>, <code>q</code>, <code>b</code>?</p>",
        "id": 377103801,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1689884566
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>b</code> is a real number, <code>p</code> and <code>q</code> are integers that have been cast to reals</p>",
        "id": 377103991,
        "sender_full_name": "shortc1rcuit",
        "timestamp": 1689884627
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>My guess: They are reals and you're applying a lemma about ordered groups (which reals are not because multiplication by a real <code>r</code> is only monotone if <code>r</code> is a real number).</p>",
        "id": 377104025,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1689884641
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So I am</p>",
        "id": 377104199,
        "sender_full_name": "shortc1rcuit",
        "timestamp": 1689884688
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If the lemma you quoted applied, you would be able to show <code>a &lt; b * (-1) &lt;-&gt; a / (-1) &lt; b</code>, namely <code>a + b &lt; 0 &lt;-&gt; 0 &lt; a + b</code>, which is of course nonsense</p>",
        "id": 377104408,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1689884751
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah I want an ordered field</p>",
        "id": 377104557,
        "sender_full_name": "shortc1rcuit",
        "timestamp": 1689884795
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You instead need <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=div_lt_iff#doc\">docs#div_lt_iff</a>, which requires you to prove <code>0 &lt; q</code></p>",
        "id": 377104563,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1689884798
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So <code>div_lt_iff</code></p>",
